lead_paragraph: The fourth season finale of “The Bachelorette” delivered Monday’s highest ratings, lifting ABC to No. 1 for the night overall. According to Nielsen’s estimates, the two-hour conclusion of the reality dating series, a spin-off of “The Bachelor,” attracted 9.5 million viewers, leading during both the 8 and 9 p.m. time slots.

headline.main: Ratings: ‘The Bachelorette’ Raises Up ABC On Gossamer Wings Of Love
